OgreKit (GNUstep) INSTALL
=========================

Required software
-----------------

You need to have the GNUstep core libraries installed in order to
compile and use OgreKit. The core packages are, at a minimum:

   * gnustep-make

   * gnustep-base

See <http://www.gnustep.org/> for further information.

You also need to have OniGuruma library installed:

    * libonig 5 or higher
      If OniGuruma is not packaged for your host system, it is available in 
      Etoile repository at etoile/trunk/Dependencies/oniguruma5.
      You can also compile against libonig 4.0.1 (or higher 4.x releases), see 
      Build and Install

See <http://www.geocities.jp/kosako3/oniguruma/> for further information.


Build and Install
-----------------

Square brackets "[ ]" are used to indicate optional parameters.

   Steps to build:

   * make [old=yes]

   * [sudo [-E]] make install

Only specifies 'old=yes' argument to build against OniGuruma 4.x releases.


Trouble
-------

Give us feedback! Tell us what you like; tell us what you think
could be better. Send bug reports and patches to <etoile-track@gna.org>.
